text.tspan: Principles on How to Be a Proper Human Being—Making Friends
We don’t need those kinds of friends
And we don’t need to be with them;
They’ll only hurt us in the end, they’re bad company.
Don’t be afraid to say, “Goodbye” to bad company.
What kind of friends then should we play with,
Have overnight, or spend the day with?
Those who are going the right way; they’re good company.
Those who are going the right way are good company.
